-- 
Majestic, Workers’ Compensation Insurer, Files Bankruptcy

-- B y   T i f f a n y   K a r y
-- 
2011-04-29T22:36:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/majestic-workers-compensation-insurer-files-bankruptcy-1-.html
Majestic Capital Ltd. (MAJC) , a workers’
compensation insurance provider, filed for bankruptcy in
Poughkeepsie,  New York , court today.  The insurer listing up to $50 million in debt in the
Chapter 11 filing, joined by five affiliates. The company
announced a delay in filing its annual report and delisted its
stock from the Nasdaq stock market this month.  Majestic’s insurance is offered to employers in California,
New York,  New Jersey , Arizona, Nevada, and other states,
according to its Web site. A downgrade from A.M. Best Co. in
March said the company had “continued deterioration in its
overall earnings,” according to a press release from Majestic,
based in Hamilton, Bermuda.  According to its annual report April 22, the company had
more than 1,032 policyholders with average annual workers’
compensation primary insurance policy premium of $87 thousand,
as of December 31, 2010. Total assets were listed as $436.19
million as of that date, according to the filing.  The case is In re Majestic Capital Ltd, 11-36225,  U.S.
Bankruptcy Court , Southern District of New York (Poughkeepsie).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tiffany Kary in New York at 
 tkary@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Pickering at 
 jpickering@bloomberg.net . 